transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hello. Can you hear me?

Speaker 1: Yes, I can.

Speaker 2: Great. I need your help. I ordered your score blue to test it,

Speaker 1: and I only wanted the original order, and now I continue to get more,

Speaker 2: and I did not authorize that, so I want to give you my name.

Speaker 1: Yeah, what's your name?

Speaker 2: John Jevely, birthdate 7H49.

Speaker 1: G as in good, I-L-V like Victor, E-L-I, G-I-L-V-E-L-I.

Speaker 2: All right, John, let me see what's going on here.

Speaker 1: Okay, I see here you just got the second order.

Speaker 2: They set you up on our VIP prescription to receive multiple pills or multiple refills.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can cancel that out for you.

Speaker 2: Before I did, I wanted to let you know we do have a service

Speaker 1: that allows me to pause that for you for up to six months at a time.

Speaker 2: If you did want to keep your prescription active

Speaker 1: and place orders in the future manually online or over the phone,

Speaker 2: as we are the only FDA approved vendors of this medication,

Speaker 1: so just wanted to let you know that before I did pause that for you.

Speaker 2: I'm good with staying in touch, and if I like your product, ordering more.

Speaker 1: I just am 100% against being sent things automatically,

Speaker 2: and then, like, for example, I just received a bottle,

Speaker 1: and could you tell me what I was charged for this?

Speaker 2: I just got it today.

Speaker 1: How much?

Speaker 2: $63.95.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I will not send this back.

Speaker 1: I will keep this, but will you stop all automatic orders?

Speaker 2: Yeah, absolutely, absolutely.

Speaker 1: I can do that for you, John.

Speaker 2: But like I was saying, what I could do for you if you wanted

Speaker 1: was pause that account for the six months.

Speaker 2: That would be until July.

Speaker 1: So you don't have to get an order in July.

Speaker 2: You would just have to, like you said, just reach out to us

Speaker 1: and let us know if you needed it by then before that next date

Speaker 2: in order to keep the account active if you wanted to go that route.

Speaker 1: I just don't want anything where I have to remember to cancel it,

Speaker 2: and then it shows up, you know.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so you would have to reach out to us before July

Speaker 2: or else it would go out.

Speaker 1: If not, I would have to cancel it for you today, which I can do.

Speaker 2: I just wouldn't be able to fill the prescription for you again in the future

Speaker 1: if I did.

Speaker 2: No, let's go ahead and just cancel it.

Speaker 1: That's fine.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 1: So I'm going to take care of that for you now.

Speaker 2: And you are all set, John.

Speaker 1: Your account has been canceled out, so you won't get anything else.

Speaker 2: You won't be billed again, okay?

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thanks.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
